just_use plays.go

# label: WORKHORSE
# role: encodes domain knowledge

The "play" concept layered on top of raw game_events: a mechanical move
PLUS strategic metadata (trick_id, description, highlighted cards, note).
Two tables, one transaction — mechanical half writes to game_events
verbatim so old replay code keeps working; strategic half writes to
lynrummy_plays keyed on event_id. New games use this endpoint; old
game_events stay readable without the annotation.

Annotation via PATCH /gopher/plays/{event_id} lets any player in the game
edit the note later.
